    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Family containing over 8,000 genera and 10,000 species of perennial plants with long, cylindrical leaves that have been used for making paper, ropes, baskets, and fabric; many also produce edible grain, the most important food sources worldwide.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
